{# ── ORIGIN ── #}
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-split">
      <div>
        <span class="section-label">The Origin</span>
        <h2>Where StageHaus Comes From</h2>
        <p>StageHaus was founded by Shelby Wayne — a producer, manager, and logistics operator with 10+ years of experience across live events, artist management, and production. Based in Tulsa, booking nationwide, and built on a foundation of real relationships and real work.</p>
        <p>The name came from the culture. StageHaus is where the work happens — backstage, in the advance call, on the production floor, at the merch table. It's the operational layer that makes the art possible, and it's where Shelby has spent a decade building the skills and relationships that StageHaus is now built on.</p>
        <p>The company is in its first chapter. That means intentional growth, strong fundamentals, and a long-term view. Every artist we work with, every show we advance, every system we build — it's all in service of becoming the production company that festivals and artists call when the stakes are high.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-split__cards">
        <div class="card" style="grid-column: span 2; border-color: var(--electric-rim); background: var(--electric-dim);">
          <span class="section-label">The Standard</span>
          <blockquote style="margin-top: .75rem; font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2vw, 1.3rem); line-height: 1.65;">
            "The best production is invisible. Nobody in the crowd thinks about load-in. They just feel the moment. That's the goal — do the work so completely that the only thing anyone experiences is the music."
          </blockquote>
        </div>
        <div class="stats-pair">
          <div class="stats-pair__item">
            <div class="stats-pair__num stats-pair__num--ivory">10+</div>
            <div class="stats-pair__label">Years of Experience</div>
            <p class="stats-pair__sub">Across live events, touring, and management</p>
          </div>
          <div class="stats-pair__item">
            <div class="stats-pair__num stats-pair__num--electric">5</div>
            <div class="stats-pair__label">Active Services</div>
