{# ── FESTIVAL LINEAGE ── #}
<section class="section section--dark">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header section-header--center">
      <span class="section-label">Festival Lineage</span>
      <h2>The Culture That Shaped the Company</h2>
      <p>StageHaus is built for a specific world — the festivals that define what live music can be when production, art, and community are all treated as equally important. These are the benchmarks.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid-3" style="margin-top: var(--s12);">

      <div class="card card--lift">
        <div class="card__icon">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polygon points="12 2 2 7 12 12 22 7 12 2"/>
            <polyline points="2 12 12 17 22 12"/>
            <polyline points="2 17 12 22 22 17"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 style="font-size: var(--fs-xl);">Electric Forest</h3>
        <p style="font-size: var(--fs-sm);">The gold standard for production-meets-art. From Ranch Arena to the forest installations, Electric Forest proves that the logistical and the magical aren't opposites — they're the same thing done right. That's the operating philosophy at StageHaus.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card card--lift">
        <div class="card__icon">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/>
            <circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/>
            <path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/>
            <path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 style="font-size: var(--fs-xl);">Bonnaroo</h3>
        <p style="font-size: var(--fs-sm);">The benchmark for community-driven festivals at scale. Bonnaroo showed what happens when logistics, culture, and artist experience are treated as core product — not afterthoughts. The bar it set for what a well-run festival looks like is one StageHaus holds itself to.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card card--lift">
        <div class="card__icon">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 style="font-size: var(--fs-xl);">Lost Lands</h3>
        <p style="font-size: var(--fs-sm);">A fully realized world — the Prehistoric Stage, Wompy Woods, over a million watts of bass, and an immersive theme that turns Legend Valley into something else entirely. Lost Lands is what happens when a single vision is executed without compromise. That level of production is the aspiration.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="card" style="margin-top: var(--s8); border-color: var(--electric-rim);">
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: var(--s12); align-items: center;">
        <div>
          <span class="section-label">The Genre DNA</span>
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--fs-2xl); margin-top: var(--s3); margin-bottom: var(--s4);">EDM, Funk, Bass, Jam — and Everything Between</h3>
          <p style="font-size: var(--fs-sm);">The StageHaus sound spectrum is wide on purpose. EDM energy and jam band soul. Bass music and funk roots. The crossover between genres is where the most interesting artists live — and where StageHaus has the deepest experience and the clearest vision for what great production looks like.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li class="feature-list__item">
